annotation.TEXT: To be continued...
Can I destroy this table with a spin jump? Nah, maybe I have to be big to do that.
Huh. Can I end up inside the wall right there?
BGM: CUSTOM - My Silent Swedish Love (arranged)

Oh, and now we've got a lottery of sorts, where I have to hit the correct blocks first in order to claim my prizes. (But, if I screw up, I could hit the T-switch to claim the 1-ups anyway, since it'll behave like a blue T-switch now.)
I'm not gonna make it, but at least I found a hidden 1-up before time ran out!
Bah. Can I run up that wall with that block in the way?
Huh. How do I break that cracked block? With a spin jump, perhaps? Oh, yep.
I forgot about that hidden mushroom again.
BGM: Super Mario 64 - Peach's Castle
D'oh! Maybe I should've chosen a different block to leave alone. Alright, I'll get in there this time!
Yay, I got a 1-up!
Maybe if I shell jump? Maybe if I duck and shell jump?
There's an ! block embedded in the wall there, possibly to warn me about the spike just above.
Space-time rewind count: 1
Alright, so here's the overworld, and I can go to either Luigis House (which should probably have an apostrophe added to "Luigis"), or Sky Garden. Let's go to Luigis House first.
Wow, that's weird looking. Also, the pause and power up sound effects seem a bit odd, maybe due to the custom music.
Huh, is that gray bar blocked by munchers (that I'll obviously have to use that silver T-switch to get past) the pipe? Well, I remember coming out of a gray bar when I started the level.
But first, is there anything good to drink in the fridge?
BGM: Yoshi's Island: SMW2 - Course Clear
Alright, now to finally investigate this pipe behind the munchers (and glitch the T-switch into the next room with me)!
BGM: Fire Emblem: Blazing Sword - Winds Across Plains

Now it's true I could've avoided getting trapped if I had left at least one of those coin blocks unrevealed, but honestly, the player shouldn't end up stuck just for filling out the entire coin block bridge. You should add a block or vine to that vertical drop to allow the player to get out.
Bah. It's annoying how if there's something grabbable close enough to the top of the wall Mario's running up, he'll grab it but fall back down.
Alright, there it is... Wait a minute, that's a T-switch, not a P-switch! Well, it probably functions just the same.
Whoops. I was holding down there when I touched that vine.
Okay, now let's take this T-switch, and... and... umm...
Huh. My mushroom got stuck in the ceiling there, but only briefly, since there was a sloped portion of the ceiling that the mushroom could fall through.
Okay, where did I pop out at? ...Oof!
Oh, I just noticed that I'm not actually scoring points, just like in COLLAB. Is there a reason the scoring doesn't work? Like, was the score display meant to be used for some other purpose?
There's another embedded ! block, but what's it warning me about? The fact that this bullet cannon actually shoots? Maybe.
Hmm... So there's a strange guy wearing a hat just like mine... Yeah, that's totally not suspicious at all, but I'm still gonna check this out.
So, I guess we've got hidden blocks, with certain ones containing 1-ups.
So, we've got some weird floating water with some weird volume on the swimming sound effects.
AHHH!!! My hat is gone! Where's my hat?! This is a disaster! Now I'll take extra damage from anything that hits me!
It would probably sound better if "recognizes" was changed to "realizes".
Demo count: 1
Yeah, but then a yellow koopa will show up at the worst time...
Argh! There's the fifth Yoshi head, but I need the silver T-switch to reach it. This'll be time-consuming, but I've gotta be very close to the goal now, so I should be alright if I'm fast...
Hmm... Maybe you should ask a vulture, a snowman, and a monkey first...
Oh, what? There's still more to the level? This is bad!
Somehow, I forgot about the hidden mushroom right there.
Okay, I'm back to this point, and now what I think I'll do is try to rack up some extra lives using the silver T-switch on the enemies!
Meh, I wanted to jam that shell in there because... reasons.

Also, I'm running out of time, but I got four of the Yoshi heads already (with the fourth one on the status bar being shown in a different color for some reason), so I can't be too far from the goal, right?
Ack! Yeah, I ended up inside the wall alright, but those slope tiles are actually solid blocks, so the game crushed me. That death seems kind of unfair.
Oh, geez. Something is wrong with this port of Winds Across Plains. It's got some screwed up notes in it.
And, there's the goal. Argh, I was pretty close to it the first time, but I just didn't have enough time on the clock...
I don't remember this guy being a splitting Chuck before. (But, looking back, I think he split up well before I got to him, and his copies must've despawned off the top.)
If only I immediately went the right way after leaving the bonus room, and if only I didn't have to waste so much time on the fifth Yoshi head...
BGM: Mario Kart: Super Circuit - Sky Garden
Ooh, thanks for the warning! That would've been very bad if people that were uninterested in green mushrooms wandered into that pipe by accident!
Oops. I forgot to put in a transition effect there by accident. Oh, well. Okay, I've rewound back to before I got trapped, and this time, I'll avoid hitting one of the coin blocks.
Nuts. Oh, I could've tried to wall jump there if I had known I was gonna clip the wall.
Alright, shortcut time! Now, obviously, you're meant to go around in circles here until you reach the T-switch in the middle. I will take that T-switch with me, in case it'll be useful later.
3-life combo! Aw, it wasn't quite as good as I had hoped. Oh, well. Let's move onto that next area, with plenty of time remaining this time.
I thought I saw something when I spin jumped on that first duder. The resulting puff of smoke says "Puff".
I wonder what the deal is with that sideways cannon on the wall there. Probably just for decoration.
What, a difficulty selection again? Is this a common thing for all of Neidave's hacks? Well anyway, I'll start with Normal for now.
Whoa, koopa, get out of my way!
Whoa, what's with the blue gradient background on the "Time Up!" screen? That's kind of neat.
Insert an apostrophe into "Im" here. Also, add "going to be" or "gonna be" before "home", and reword the last sentence so it sounds better.
Gee, I wonder if there are hidden coin blocks here that I'll need to reveal... Also, I found a hidden mushroom over here on the right.
Tush! Whoa, I wasn't trying to kick the shell there, but at least nothing got killed before being transformed into a silver coin!
What, a Yoshi head? I guess that's what represents the Yoshi coins in this hack. Also, what the heck is that? A nibbled-on mushroom?
Oh, what? I have to start all over? Yeah, because there wasn't a midpoint in this level (at least I didn't find one). Grumble... Grumble... Alright, let's speed this footage up.
Tush!
Huh, I caught the wall again there. Maybe I should intentionally try to wall jump every time I bump into a wall in midair, in case it'll work.
Demo count: 2
BGM: Sonic & Knuckles - Sky Sanctuary Zone
Tush! (As opposed to "Push!", because it's a T-switch, not a P-switch. I had to point this out, because otherwise, I'd have people thinking "Tush!" was a typo.)
Oh, looks like I'll need to find a P-switch in order to go that way.
Man, that one level took a while. I'm gonna stop here for now.
And, since his other hacks appeared to be short, I decided that, sure, I'd do them. Now, just be aware that this one is only a 1-world demo at this time.
Alright, let's enter Sky Garden now.
Alright, let's just enter Luigis House now.
Hello, and welcome to... Mario's Search For His Hat! It's by Neidave, who requested that I play his other hacks after I was done with COLLAB.
Alright, another Yoshi head. That makes three. I'm glad I didn't waste time after activating that T-switch.
Now, let's see... I did leave these guys back here alive, so this is where I'll start the combo.
Ooh, I love this music! Let's hope it's not screwed up somewhere!
Goal tape average so far: 40 / 1 = 40 stars each.
Alright, I'm getting sick of this, so I'm gonna try to break the next room using this T-switch, which'll act blue when I take it through the pipe.
Well, I'm still lucky right now, but how long will my luck hold out?
Wow, I got every 1-up, and without knowing where they were, and without using my T-switch. What are the odds? (Somebody will calculate the odds, right?)
Alright, time to go to ludicrous speed!
Alright, that's it for the title demo, so let's get started.
Uh, dude? How am I supposed to get back? I don't think you designed this part properly, and now I'm stuck.
Can I open this thing? Does that map on the wall mark the location of any hidden treasure?
Okay, let me guess... The slope here is actually a wall triangle, so I can run up this wall, right? Yep. Also, I'd better watch out for the bullet cannons that aren't just mere decorations.
Up next is a red level, so I guess you guys can vote on whether I take the normal path or the secret path after I get both exits in it.
Yay! I got lucky there! However, there's no way I'll get that lucky on the next one, right?
At this point, I realize that I've been here before, and I'm going the wrong way. Also, I briefly forget that the T-switch now acts like a blue one when I try to use it on the enemies here. Oops.
Tush!
Alright, got 'em all! Now, let's hope the goal is just up ahead...
